{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FWK3nZoJGtqVZnezdriPdy","type":"tool_result","content":"  4475→- **Holding state in memory across loop iterations** without a freshness check is the root cause of the corruption bug. State should be read-modify-write with version checking.\n  4476→- **Running `npm test` twice in verification** (once for full output, once grep-filtered) wastes tokens. Capture once, filter from capture.\n  4477→\n  4478→## Action Items\n  4479→\n  4480→| Priority | Action | Status |\n  4481→|----------|--------|--------|\n  4482→| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint or close out. | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4483→| **P0** | Fix Ralph state corruption — add compare-and-swap or monotonic version to state writes | CRITICAL — 35+ occurrences, $150-250 estimated waste |\n  4484→| **P0** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CRITICAL — stops wasting sessions |\n  4485→| **P1** | Make verification -> done status transition atomic with commit | Reinforced by session 32 gap |\n  4486→| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($224.38, 25.7%) | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4487→| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD — 3/4 verifications ran npm test twice |\n  4488→| **P2** | Tier verification depth by story complexity | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4489→| **P2** | Add bash version check or shellcheck enforcement for ralph scripts | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4490→| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4491→| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story references from tracking data | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4492→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014XSrysGGxcC8uucVkNsuL5","session_id":"1a7a6ebc-c4c8-4915-89a8-1d1ede2eb61d","uuid":"3467a865-c924-4870-b2c7-39e23799ecea","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:32:05.855Z"}
